00:31.715 --> 00:32.847
Surprise!

00:32.849 --> 00:35.150
(CHUCKLES)
Not yet, Olaf.

00:35.619 --> 00:37.252
Surprise!
(WOMEN GASP)

00:37.254 --> 00:39.120
WOMEN: Not yet, Olaf.

00:40.090 --> 00:41.556
Surprise!
(GASPS)

00:41.558 --> 00:43.858
(SIGHS) Not yet, Olaf.

00:47.330 --> 00:49.197
Whoa!

00:49.766 --> 00:51.332
Hello!

00:51.701 --> 00:53.501
Surprise!
(GASPS)

00:53.503 --> 00:55.837
(CHUCKLES) Olaf! Not yet!

00:55.839 --> 00:56.771
ELSA: Anna's right.

00:56.773 --> 00:59.007
Our surprise holiday party
doesn't start

00:59.009 --> 01:01.476
until after
the Jule bell rings.

01:01.478 --> 01:04.345
Sorry, the suspense
is tearing me apart.

01:04.346 --> 01:05.647
Thank you!

01:05.715 --> 01:06.681
(CHUCKLES)
I'm excited too, Olaf.

01:06.683 --> 01:09.951
This is Arendelle's
first Christmas in forever.

01:09.953 --> 01:12.287
The first of many to come.

01:12.289 --> 01:14.522
Elsa, look!
They're arriving!

01:14.524 --> 01:15.557
<i> ♪ Look at everyone</i>

01:15.559 --> 01:17.292
<i>♪ They don't realize</i>
(GASPS) What?

01:17.294 --> 01:20.595
<i>♪ We planned a party</i>
<i>as a big surprise</i>

01:20.597 --> 01:24.432
<i>♪ Soon the ballroom will echo</i>
<i>With sounds of cheer</i>

01:24.434 --> 01:28.503
<i> ♪ As we ring in</i>
<i> the season this year</i>

01:28.505 --> 01:29.838
<i> ♪ This is overdue</i>

01:29.840 --> 01:31.339
<i>♪ Gotta look our best</i>
Ooh!

01:31.341 --> 01:34.742
<i> ♪ I've never been</i>
<i> so nicely dressed</i>

01:34.744 --> 01:36.611
<i> ♪ We'll be hosting</i>
<i> and toasting</i>

01:36.613 --> 01:37.912
<i> ♪ The whole night through</i>

01:37.914 --> 01:42.016
<i> ♪ As we ring in</i>
<i> the season with you</i>

01:42.018 --> 01:44.886
<i>♪ It's the first Christmas</i>
<i>in forever</i>

01:44.888 --> 01:48.056
<i> ♪ Since we opened up</i>
<i> the gate</i>

01:48.058 --> 01:51.726
<i>♪ And it's the first Christmas</i>
<i>I remember to date</i>

01:51.728 --> 01:55.997
<i> ♪ And it's already</i>
<i> worth the wait</i>

01:55.999 --> 01:57.031
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:57.033 --> 01:58.666
<i> ♪ Look at all the joy</i>
<i> ♪ All the joy</i>

01:58.668 --> 02:00.568
<i> ♪ And it's everywhere</i>
<i> ♪ Everywhere</i>

02:00.570 --> 02:02.937
<i> ♪ I feel the Christmas spirit</i>
<i> in the air</i>

02:02.939 --> 02:03.605
<i> ♪ Feel the spirit</i>

02:03.607 --> 02:06.975
<i> ♪ And the party will start</i>
<i> At the strike of noon</i>

02:06.977 --> 02:12.113
<i> ♪ And we'll ring</i>
<i> in the season so soon</i>

02:12.115 --> 02:14.983
OLAF: Hey!
It's Kristoff and Sven!

02:14.985 --> 02:17.452
(GASPS) And the Jule bell!

02:17.454 --> 02:19.354
Why am I so excited
about that?

02:19.356 --> 02:20.788
Olaf,
the Jule bell signals

02:20.790 --> 02:23.825
the start of the holidays
in Arendelle.

02:23.827 --> 02:24.158
Ooh!

02:24.160 --> 02:30.198
<i> ♪ And it's almost time</i>
<i> to ring the bell</i>

02:30.200 --> 02:36.004
<i> ♪ We'll hear it chime</i>
<i> through Arendelle</i>

02:36.072 --> 02:38.840
<i> ♪ It's finally here</i>
<i> and it's happening fast</i>

02:38.842 --> 02:43.044
<i>♪ We'll make up for all</i>
<i>We have missed in the past</i>

02:43.046 --> 02:45.446
<i> ♪ It's time to celebrate</i>

02:45.448 --> 02:50.752
<i> ♪ As we ring in the season</i>

02:51.821 --> 02:54.856
<i> ♪ At last ♪</i>

02:54.858 --> 02:56.791
(TOLLING)

02:59.095 --> 03:01.863
Let the holidays begin!

03:01.865 --> 03:02.997
(CHEERING)

03:02.999 --> 03:04.265
Okay, now!

03:04.267 --> 03:06.301
(CHUCKLES) Surprise!

03:06.303 --> 03:07.568
(GASPS)

03:07.704 --> 03:09.737
OLAF: Uh-oh.
Wait, wait, wait.

03:09.739 --> 03:12.273
Hold on, hold on.
Going so soon?

03:12.275 --> 03:12.807
The Jule bell rang.

03:12.809 --> 03:15.343
I must get home
for my family's
holiday tradition...

03:15.345 --> 03:16.411
rolling the lefse.
Um...

03:16.413 --> 03:18.746
Ours is putting out porridge
for the Tomte.

03:18.748 --> 03:21.082
We're making traditional
bordstabelbakkels!

03:21.084 --> 03:24.686
And I'm gonna filet
the krumsakringlekakke!

03:24.688 --> 03:26.254
That's a thing, right?

03:26.256 --> 03:27.188
Oh, Mr. and Mrs. Olsen?

03:27.190 --> 03:30.458
You're welcome to join us
in the castle if you'd like.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.759
Thank you, Your Majesty.

03:31.761 --> 03:33.594
But Olga and I
should be getting home

03:33.596 --> 03:36.130
to knit socks
for our grandchildren.

03:36.132 --> 03:37.265
It's our tradition.

03:37.267 --> 03:40.101
(LAUGHS) Yes.
And we wouldn't
want to intrude

03:40.103 --> 03:42.737
on your family traditions.

03:43.473 --> 03:44.272
(SIGHS)

03:44.274 --> 03:48.176
Oh, so the surprise
is everyone left.

03:48.178 --> 03:50.945
Hey, I say it's their loss.

03:50.947 --> 03:52.814
Who needs
a big party anyway?

03:52.816 --> 03:53.281
Kristoff?

03:53.283 --> 03:55.116
I've got just the thing
to cheer you up:

03:55.118 --> 03:58.686
my favorite traditional
troll tradition.

03:58.688 --> 04:00.855
Care to join in?
Uh, yeah!

04:00.857 --> 04:03.524
Okay, it starts
with a gathering song,

04:03.526 --> 04:06.427
"The Ballad of Flemmingrad."

04:06.429 --> 04:07.562
I love ballads!

04:07.564 --> 04:10.365
<i>♪ Every December</i>
<i>we all gather round</i>

04:10.367 --> 04:14.202
<i>♪ To pay our respects</i>
<i>To a troll so renowned</i>

04:14.204 --> 04:17.105
<i> ♪ In remembrance</i>
<i> of the friend we had</i>

04:17.107 --> 04:20.641
<i> ♪ A jolly old soul</i>
<i> we called Flemmingrad</i>

04:20.642 --> 04:20.908
Tempo!

04:20.910 --> 04:23.711
<i> ♪ We all dig deep down</i>
<i> And we uproot the past</i>

04:23.713 --> 04:27.415
<i>♪ We shove up its nostrils</i>
<i>A fistful of grass</i>

04:27.417 --> 04:27.915
Nostrils?

04:27.917 --> 04:33.388
<i> ♪ We shape his likeness</i>
<i> Bless his soul</i>

04:34.557 --> 04:35.656
(SHRIEKS)

04:35.658 --> 04:36.324
Whoa, gross.

04:36.326 --> 04:42.563
<i> ♪ Oh Flemmy</i>
<i> The fungus troll ♪</i>

04:44.534 --> 04:46.968
Now, you lick his forehead
and make a wish.

04:46.970 --> 04:48.302
(LICKS) Who's next?

04:48.304 --> 04:50.171
Elsa, you're up.
(GAGS)

04:50.173 --> 04:52.240
Come on.
Tastes like lichen.

04:52.242 --> 04:54.208
You're a princess.
You don't have to settle.

04:54.210 --> 04:57.545
Okay. Not so much
a royal activity.
I get it.

04:57.547 --> 05:01.215
But wait until you taste
my traditional Flemmy stew.

05:01.217 --> 05:04.952
It may smell like wet fur,
but it's a real
crowd pleaser.

05:04.954 --> 05:06.154
Oh, thanks.
We're good.

05:06.156 --> 05:08.623
Big breakfast.
(CHUCKLES)

05:08.725 --> 05:09.791
(OLAF EXCLAIMS)

05:09.793 --> 05:11.426
(CHUCKLES) I can't wait!

05:11.428 --> 05:12.493
ELSA: For what, Olaf?

05:12.495 --> 05:14.729
For your family tradition.
What is it?

05:14.731 --> 05:16.798
Tell me, tell me,
tell me!

05:18.601 --> 05:21.469
Do we have
any traditions, Elsa?

05:22.972 --> 05:24.906
Do you remember?

05:27.177 --> 05:30.878
Well, I remember...

05:30.880 --> 05:33.114
<i> ♪ It was long ago</i>

05:33.116 --> 05:35.349
<i> ♪ They would ring the bell</i>

05:35.351 --> 05:40.855
<i> ♪ We could hear it chime</i>
<i> through Arendelle</i>

05:40.857 --> 05:46.627
<i> ♪ I remember the way</i>
<i> that I felt back then</i>

05:46.629 --> 05:51.766
<i> ♪ We would ring in</i>
<i> the season</i>

05:51.835 --> 05:58.306
<i> ♪ We would ring in</i>
<i> the season ♪</i>

06:00.076 --> 06:03.744
But the Jule bell was
for the kingdom.

06:03.746 --> 06:05.379
What about us?

06:05.515 --> 06:10.518
After the gates were closed,
we were never together.

06:10.520 --> 06:11.853
(SIGHS)

06:11.855 --> 06:12.954
Elsa?

06:12.956 --> 06:14.322
ELSA: I'm sorry, Anna.

06:14.324 --> 06:17.391
It's my fault we don't have
a family tradition.

06:17.393 --> 06:18.759
Wait, Elsa...

06:21.631 --> 06:23.164
(SIGHS)

06:24.801 --> 06:26.501
(OLAF WHIMPER)

06:29.105 --> 06:29.871
(GASPS)

06:29.873 --> 06:33.474
Sven! Anna and Elsa
don't have a family tradition.

06:33.476 --> 06:34.408
(WHIMPERS)

06:34.410 --> 06:35.643
I know it's sad...

06:35.645 --> 06:37.378
but I have a solution!

06:37.380 --> 06:38.913
We'll go and find
the best tradition

06:38.915 --> 06:40.681
Anna and Elsa
have ever seen...

06:40.683 --> 06:42.416
and bring it back
to the castle!

06:42.418 --> 06:44.152
Are you with me?

06:44.154 --> 06:45.253
Ow!

06:45.255 --> 06:48.890
Let's go
find their tradition!

06:50.360 --> 06:52.126
House number one.

06:53.396 --> 06:55.296
Wow, festive.

06:56.199 --> 06:57.732
WOMAN: Coming!

06:58.067 --> 07:00.134
Good afternoon.
I am Olaf, and...

07:00.136 --> 07:00.568
Hey, Olaf!

07:00.570 --> 07:03.171
Please let me finish,
and I like warm hugs.

07:03.173 --> 07:04.572
This is my associate, Sven.

07:04.574 --> 07:07.175
We're going door to door
looking for
family traditions.

07:07.177 --> 07:10.244
Tell us yours,
and we'll decide if
it's special enough.

07:10.246 --> 07:12.747
Oh! We make
candy canes together.

07:12.916 --> 07:14.081
Ooh!

07:14.417 --> 07:15.816
(CHUCKLES)

07:15.818 --> 07:16.751
Sugar rush!

07:16.753 --> 07:18.553
You're supposed to eat it.

07:18.555 --> 07:21.489
Eat my new nose?
Why would I do that?

07:21.491 --> 07:24.659
Because it's that time
of year!

07:24.661 --> 07:25.459
Hmm.

07:25.461 --> 07:28.629
It's that time of year!

07:37.340 --> 07:37.939
(CLEARS THROAT)

07:37.941 --> 07:41.842
<i> ♪ Happy, merry, holly, jolly</i>
<i> Season's greetings here</i>

07:41.844 --> 07:44.445
<i> ♪ I'm wondering</i>
<i> what your family does</i>

07:44.447 --> 07:46.113
<i> ♪ At that time of year</i>

07:46.115 --> 07:48.082
<i> ♪ Love and joy</i>
<i> and peace on earth</i>

07:48.084 --> 07:49.717
<i> ♪ And tidings of good cheer</i>

07:49.719 --> 07:51.953
<i> ♪ Do you</i>
<i> have tradition things</i>

07:51.955 --> 07:53.688
<i>♪ For that time of year?</i>

07:53.690 --> 07:55.923
<i>♪ Well, we hang up</i>
<i>boughs of evergreen</i>

07:55.925 --> 07:57.592
<i> ♪ On every single doorway</i>

07:57.594 --> 08:01.162
<i>♪ Bake a giant cookie</i>
<i>In the wavy shape of Norway</i>

08:01.164 --> 08:05.066
<i> ♪ Go from door</i>
<i> to door to door</i>
<i> Wassailing with our choir!</i>

08:05.068 --> 08:10.838
<i> ♪ Hang up</i>
<i> all your giant socks</i>
<i> Above an open fire</i>

08:10.840 --> 08:12.840
That sounds safe.

08:12.842 --> 08:15.142
<i> ♪ So happy, merry,</i>
<i> yuletide carol</i>

08:15.144 --> 08:16.944
<i> ♪ Faithful friends are deer</i>

08:16.946 --> 08:18.312
<i>♪ Thanks for sharing</i>
<i>what you do</i>

08:18.314 --> 08:22.216
<i> ♪ At that time of year</i>
(CLOCK CHIMES)

08:22.218 --> 08:23.351
(GASPS) We better get
a move on

08:23.353 --> 08:26.420
if we're gonna hit
every house in the kingdom.

08:26.522 --> 08:26.854
(NEIGHS)

08:26.856 --> 08:30.424
<i> ♪ Jolly, merry, happy, holly</i>
<i> On a midnight clear</i>

08:30.426 --> 08:32.659
<i> ♪ I'm here to ask you</i>
<i> what you do</i>

08:32.662 --> 08:34.128
<i> ♪ At that time of year</i>

08:34.130 --> 08:37.832
<i>♪ Hi, shalom, happy solstice</i>
<i>Fancy chandelier</i>

08:37.833 --> 08:39.967
<i> ♪ I'm looking</i>
<i> for tradition stuff</i>

08:39.969 --> 08:41.635
<i> ♪ For that time of year</i>

08:41.638 --> 08:43.169
<i> ♪ Well, we make</i>
<i> our decorations</i>

08:43.172 --> 08:45.139
<i> ♪ Out of flotsam and jetsam</i>

08:45.141 --> 08:46.440
<i> ♪ Bake a yummy fruitcake</i>

08:46.442 --> 08:49.377
<i> ♪ And you can't leave</i>
<i> till you get some</i>

08:49.379 --> 08:50.878
That went right through me.

08:50.880 --> 08:51.979
<i>♪ Buy each other presents</i>

08:51.981 --> 08:53.748
<i>♪ And then hide them</i>
<i>very nimbly</i>

08:53.750 --> 08:57.785
<i> ♪ Wait up for a chubby man</i>
<i> To shimmy down your chimney</i>

08:57.787 --> 09:00.354
Breaking and entering:
okay on Christmas.

09:00.356 --> 09:02.990
<i> ♪ Oh, happy,</i>
<i> merry mule-tied barrels</i>

09:02.992 --> 09:04.258
<i>♪ Faithful, gladsome cheer</i>

09:04.260 --> 09:06.927
<i> ♪ And thanks for sharing</i>
<i> what you do</i>

09:06.929 --> 09:10.698
<i> ♪ At that time of year</i>

09:10.700 --> 09:11.932
Thank you.

09:11.934 --> 09:13.301
<i> ♪ We knit scarves</i>
<i> and sweaters</i>

09:13.303 --> 09:15.303
<i>♪ And we wear</i>
<i>our matching mittens</i>

09:15.305 --> 09:16.904
<i> ♪ Don't forget</i>
<i> the jammies</i>

09:16.906 --> 09:19.440
<i> ♪ That I knitted</i>
<i> for my kittens</i>

09:19.442 --> 09:20.374
<i> ♪ Eight nights in a row</i>

09:20.376 --> 09:23.177
<i> ♪ We light menorahs</i>
<i> on our mantels</i>

09:23.179 --> 09:25.780
You cut down a tree...

09:25.782 --> 09:29.517
and then you dress
its corpse with candles.

09:29.519 --> 09:30.885
(KIDS WHIMPER)

09:32.689 --> 09:34.422
I love it!

09:37.593 --> 09:39.593
<i> ♪ Anna and Elsa</i>

09:39.595 --> 09:43.964
<i> ♪ Will have all that</i>
<i> they need</i>

09:43.966 --> 09:46.500
<i> ♪ I'll fill my sleigh here</i>

09:46.502 --> 09:49.337
<i> ♪ With the help of my steed</i>

09:49.339 --> 09:52.873
<i>♪ It'll be the best</i>
<i>time of year</i>

09:52.875 --> 09:56.110
<i> ♪ It's up to you</i>

09:56.112 --> 09:59.313
<i> ♪ Up to me</i>
<i> Me, me</i>

09:59.315 --> 10:00.548
<i> ♪ Up to...</i>

10:00.550 --> 10:01.849
<i> ♪ Mew</i>

10:02.852 --> 10:06.587
<i> ♪ Oh, happy, merry,</i>
<i> Mele Kaliki</i>

10:06.589 --> 10:09.657
<i> ♪ Holly, jolly, happy tappy</i>

10:09.659 --> 10:11.559
<i>♪ Chubby man</i>
<i>will soon appear</i>

10:11.561 --> 10:13.594
<i> ♪ And faithful friends</i>
<i> are tiny deer</i>

10:13.596 --> 10:15.763
<i>♪ And festive tidings</i>
<i>midnight clear, and...</i>

10:15.765 --> 10:18.132
Can I leave
this fruitcake here?

10:18.134 --> 10:23.671
<i> ♪ At that time of year ♪</i>

10:24.674 --> 10:26.340
(MEWS)

10:27.443 --> 10:28.075
Last house, Sven.

10:28.077 --> 10:32.747
Something tells me this will
be the best tradition yet!

10:32.849 --> 10:34.315
Yoo-hoo.

10:34.317 --> 10:35.116
Hello.

10:35.118 --> 10:39.487
And what does your family do
at that time of year?

10:39.489 --> 10:40.688
(CHUCKLES) Oh!

10:40.690 --> 10:42.056
(MUSIC PLAYING)

10:42.058 --> 10:46.093
Enjoying the Christmas sweats,
inquisitive magic snowman?

10:46.095 --> 10:47.194
Oh, yeah!

10:47.196 --> 10:50.264
Nothin' like
taking your coals off
once in a while.

10:50.266 --> 10:51.132
You know what I mean?

10:51.134 --> 10:55.136
My troubles
are just melting away.

10:55.338 --> 10:57.705
In retrospect,
the holiday sweats

10:57.707 --> 11:01.075
are for those
not made of snow.

11:01.677 --> 11:02.710
(SPLUTTERS)

11:02.712 --> 11:05.079
Oh, I feel so refreshed!
Am I glowing?

11:05.081 --> 11:07.948
(GRUNTS) Here's a sauna
for your friends.

11:07.950 --> 11:10.017
Thank you,
Mr. Wandering Oaken.

11:10.019 --> 11:10.985
Oh, one last thing.

11:10.987 --> 11:12.019
Would it be possible to get

11:12.021 --> 11:13.687
one of those
awkwardly revealing...

11:13.689 --> 11:14.922
yet tastefully
traditional towels

11:14.924 --> 11:16.457
your family is
so fond of wearing?

11:16.459 --> 11:18.159
Take mine, yeah?

11:18.628 --> 11:19.660
(DOOR CLOSES)

11:19.662 --> 11:21.362
OLAF: Still warm.

11:21.364 --> 11:23.097
<i>♪ Dashing through the snow</i>

11:23.099 --> 11:25.466
<i> ♪ With traditions</i>
<i> in our sleigh</i>

11:25.468 --> 11:29.637
<i> ♪ Back to the castle we go</i>
<i> To save this holiday</i>

11:29.639 --> 11:30.104
<i> ♪ Ho, ho, ho</i>

11:30.106 --> 11:34.675
<i> ♪ Our plan has zero flaws</i>
<i> I see nothing going wrong ♪</i>

11:34.677 --> 11:35.976
(SHRIEKS)

11:37.613 --> 11:40.147
Whew! Crisis averted.

11:41.951 --> 11:44.051
(WHISTLING)

11:49.759 --> 11:54.161
Oh, look, another reindeer
going the opposite direction.

11:54.163 --> 11:55.329
Hi!

12:12.381 --> 12:16.116
Wow, we're making
really good time!

12:22.892 --> 12:24.358
(GASPS)

12:30.800 --> 12:33.234
Hey! The fire's out.

12:33.236 --> 12:34.902
(EXPLODES)

12:34.904 --> 12:36.637
Oh, darn it.

12:42.111 --> 12:43.377
(SIGHS)

12:44.213 --> 12:45.079
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

12:45.081 --> 12:48.883
Anna, I owe you
an apology for earlier.

12:49.619 --> 12:50.651
Anna?

12:50.653 --> 12:52.219
(CLATTERS)

12:58.728 --> 13:00.461
(GASPS)
Hi, Elsa!

13:00.463 --> 13:03.030
(SIGHS) Anna!
What are you doing up here?

13:03.032 --> 13:04.798
Looking for traditions.

13:04.800 --> 13:06.133
Ooh! (CHUCKLES)

13:06.135 --> 13:08.068
And what are you wearing?

13:08.070 --> 13:09.503
My old Viking helmet...

13:09.505 --> 13:12.640
and this was
my sorceress cloak.

13:12.642 --> 13:13.541
Dragon feet!

13:13.543 --> 13:14.708
(MIMICS GROWLING)
(LAUGHS)

13:14.710 --> 13:17.745
I found them
in my old trunk.
What's in yours?

13:17.747 --> 13:19.113
Oh, mostly gloves.

13:19.115 --> 13:22.449
Right. Rows and rows
of satin gloves.

13:23.953 --> 13:24.685
Oh.

13:24.687 --> 13:27.154
Yep. Welcome to my world.

13:27.156 --> 13:29.423
Wait. Who's this little guy?

13:29.425 --> 13:32.159
